Clea: What on earth is this...

Mage Relm: It seems to be like the Shrine of Lefgaria. It
looks like quite some time has passed since it was built.

Thief Nora: Look! There are shoes and clothes scattered
around!

Mage Relm: It seems like they were offering the results of
their hunt. If that's the case, they might be nearby.

Clea: It seems like we've arrived, although I'm not sure
where we are.
Thief Nora: Leave it to me! I can see sound, you know...
Thief Nora: It's in front of us, here it comes!!
Hunter Delma: Ugh... Where is this...?
Mage Relm: Most likely, you touched a relic of Lefgaria.
Hunter Delma: Relic... Could it be a crystal...?

Mage Relm: It seems that you have been freed from the magic
of Lefgaria by being defeated and becoming prey.

Hunter Delma: ...I hate, hate that our forest was taken away
and I'm starting to remember.

Hunter Delma: I became a demon hunter by touching the
crystal.

Thief Nora: I-I don't think this person is bad! So, could
you please stop handing them over to the guards?

Clea: We were just asked to solve the problem, so there
shouldn't be any more issues, right?

Mage Relm: Let me take the clothes you were wearing just in
case. There might still be some magic residue on them.
Hunter Delma: Thank you very much. Please take this.

Thief Nora: No, even if you say beastmen, there might be a
possibility that they have allies.
Thief Nora: I just had a little bit of hope. Now, let's go!

Mage Relm: I will place the crystal just to be safe,

Mage Relm: If my prediction is correct, something... should
happen.
Thief Nora: N-Nothing is happening... Is it broken, perhaps?

Priestess Sophia: 'It's troubling, isn't it? We don't have
any other clues to go on.'
Mage Relm: That shouldn't be the case, my hypothesis is--

Clea: As Relm-san predicted, it seems to be just as
expected. However, it looks like there's an unexpected bonus
as well.

Mage Relm's illusion: Just as I thought! This crystal is
reacting to the demons' shrine!

Mage Relm's illusion: It's truly amazing... It seems like
completely unknown knowledge is flowing into me...

Mage Relm's illusion: Oh, how grateful I am to Duxa-san. He
should be amazed by these results!

Mage Relm's illusion: Next... shall we head towards the cave
in the inlet?
Clea: What on earth is this... What were we looking at?

Mage Relm: I believe it is the Albis from that time. I don't
understand the principle, but I can't think of any other
explanation.

Thief Nora: They said we're heading towards the cave in the
inlet!

Priestess Sophia: I never expected Albis-san to have such a
mischievous personality, creating illusions of demons like
this.

Mage Relm: I've become even more interested. I will
definitely meet them and confirm their knowledge of magic!
